1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:09,000
Taking walks and playing games when there's sunny weather

2
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:15,000
If there's rain, they're singing songs or reading books together

3
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:21,000
Every day just has a way of feeling extra lucky

4
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:26,000
When you spend it with a friend, just like Bjorn and Bucky

5
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:29,000
Just like Bjorn and Bucky!

6
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:35,000
Pirate story!

7
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:39,000
Lay in a course for home, roared the pirate captain

8
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:43,000
And a skull and crossbones flag rose atop the main mast

9
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:47,000
The end! Yeah!

10
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:51,000
Wow, that's so great! Oh, I want to be a pirate!

11
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:55,000
Me too! I'll be the pirate captain, and you can be my crew!

12
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:59,000
Why do you get to be captain? I would be a cool pirate captain!

13
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:02,000
Ha! You, Bjorn! You're not cut out to be a pirate captain!

14
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:04,000
I'd be an awesome captain!

15
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:07,000
No, I'm the captain! No, I'm captain!

16
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:08,000
You scarvey bear!

17
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:11,000
Boys, boys! Come on, don't fight!

18
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:13,000
Look, I baked a nice pie!

19
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:14,000
Want some!

20
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:18,000
Franny, can you not see we're in the middle of an important discussion?

21
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:21,000
Look here, Bjorn! I'm the pirate captain, and that is final!

22
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:25,000
All right! Captain your ship! I'll just have a ship of my own!

23
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:27,000
Boys!

24
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:29,000
Chicky ahoy!

25
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:32,000
Sweet! Awesome!

26
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:35,000
Yeah, I am totally a pirate captain!

27
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:37,000
The king of the seven seas!

28
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:38,000
Who's there?

29
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:43,000
Arr! Shiver me timbers! Raise the mizzenmast!

30
00:01:43,000 --> 00:01:45,000
Full speed ahead!

31
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:46,000
Arr!

32
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:47,000
Huh?

33
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:48,000
Huh?

34
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:49,000
Huh?

35
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:50,000
Huh?

36
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:51,000
Huh?

37
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:54,000
What is this bottle doing here?

38
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:55,000
Bottle, aye?

39
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:57,000
Where'd you come from?

40
00:01:57,000 --> 00:01:58,000
There's something inside!

41
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:03,000
Ooh! A treasure map!

42
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:05,000
Blimey! A treasure map!

43
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:07,000
Well, blow me down!

44
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:09,000
A circle of grass!

45
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:10,000
Yo-ho!

46
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:12,000
A pine tree without branches!

47
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:13,000
A rock!

48
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:14,000
Yar!

49
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:15,000
Aha!

50
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:19,000
Bucky eye!

51
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:21,000
That's Captain Bookbeard to you!

52
00:02:21,000 --> 00:02:22,000
Oh, is that so?

53
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:25,000
Well, I'm Captain Longbjorn Silver!

54
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:28,000
I have both a parrot and a treasure map to prove it!

55
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:29,000
No, I'm the captain!

56
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:33,000
My map is way better than that lame map that you have, fake captain!

57
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:35,000
Oh, we'll just see about that!

58
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:39,000
I'll find my treasure before you find your dumb treasure!

59
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:42,000
I know I'll find mine before you!

60
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:46,000
There's no way he'll find the treasure first!

61
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:48,000
Without my new treasure-seagoscope!

62
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:49,000
All right?

63
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:52,000
Find some treasure!

64
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:53,000
Ahoy!

65
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:54,000
Treasure!

66
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:55,000
Yeah!

67
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:56,000
Wait, what?

68
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:57,000
Curses, it'd be a rock!

69
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:00,000
Ahoy!

70
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:02,000
Nah, just an acorn!

71
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:03,000
Booty, ahoy!

72
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:04,000
Ah, blast!

73
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:06,000
It's only a mushroom!

74
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:12,000
Well, Chickie, according to the treasure map, what we're trying to find should be nearby!

75
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:13,000
Go look around!

76
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:15,000
Find the treasure, Chickie!

77
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:16,000
Find it!

78
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:18,000
Have you got it?

79
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:19,000
Did you find it?

80
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:22,000
No, Chickie, that's a strawberry!

81
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:23,000
Keep searching!

82
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:24,000
Not quite!

83
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:25,000
That's a raspberry!

84
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:26,000
Try again, please!

85
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:30,000
Those are pine cones, Chickie!

86
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:31,000
Whoa!

87
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:36,000
You are a treasure-seagoscope, not a random wrong stuff-seagoscope!

88
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:37,000
Find treasure!

89
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:38,000
You scallywag!

90
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:39,000
Whoa!

91
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:40,000
Sorry!

92
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:41,000
I didn't mean it!

93
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:42,000
Whoa!

94
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:43,000
Whoa!

95
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:44,000
Did you have any luck?

96
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:45,000
None, did you?

97
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:46,000
No, sir!

98
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:47,000
The problem is that this stupid map is useless!

99
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:48,000
That's right!

100
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:49,000
Yours and mine both are!

101
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:50,000
I've searched near every tree and found nothing!

102
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:51,000
Hey, wait a second!

103
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:52,000
Take a look, Bjorn!

104
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:53,000
Bucky!

105
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:54,000
Bucky!

106
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:55,000
Are these two halves of one bigger map?

107
00:03:55,000 --> 00:03:56,000
Huh!

108
00:03:56,000 --> 00:03:59,000
So we were looking near the wrong trees!

109
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:00,000
Arr!

110
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:01,000
Yo-ho-ho!

111
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:03,000
So why is that this stupid map is useless?

112
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:04,000
What?

113
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:05,000
What?

114
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:06,000
What?

115
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:07,000
What?

116
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:08,000
What?

117
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:09,000
What?

118
00:04:09,000 --> 00:04:10,000
What?

119
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:11,000
What?

120
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:12,000
What?

121
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:13,000
What?

122
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:14,000
What?

123
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:15,000
What?

124
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:16,000
What?

125
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:17,000
What?

126
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:18,000
What?

127
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:19,000
What?

128
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:20,000
What?

129
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:21,000
What?

130
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:23,000
So why is the ladder here?

131
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:24,000
Climb up!

132
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:25,000
I'll hold it steady!

133
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:28,000
There's something in there!

134
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:29,000
Oh!

135
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:30,000
Treasure!

136
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:32,000
It must be the treasure!

137
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:33,000
Ha-ha!

138
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:34,000
Whoa!

139
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:35,000
Look!

140
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:36,000
Dude, hi!

141
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:37,000
I guess that's why they call us pirates!

142
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:38,000
Ha-ha!

143
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:39,000
Good one, Buff!

144
00:04:39,000 --> 00:04:40,000
Hey guys!

145
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:42,000
Uh-uh-uh-uh-uh!

146
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:44,000
Hey, what are you doing here, Franny?

147
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:45,000
I-

148
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:46,000
Hang on!

149
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:47,000
Just listen to this, Franny.

150
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:51,000
We just found a genuine pirate treasure pie!

151
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:53,000
I made that pie!

152
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:56,000
I wanted to play pirates with you guys,

153
00:04:56,000 --> 00:04:58,000
but you were ignoring me.

154
00:04:58,000 --> 00:05:00,000
So I'm the one who drew the treasure map,

155
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:02,000
just like I'm the one who baked the pie!

156
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:04,000
Arr!

157
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:06,000
That's awesome, Franny!

158
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:10,000
This turned out to be the tastiest pirate story ever!

159
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:14,000
Isn't that right, Longbjorn Silver?

160
00:05:14,000 --> 00:05:18,000
Yep, you're absolutely correct about that,

161
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:20,000
my dear Captain Buckbeard!

162
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:22,000
What happened to our pie?

163
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:29,000
Bring that back, you rapscallion!

